&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 5 Staff Nurse - Fracture Clinic, Orthopaedic Outpatients and Plaster Room&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full Time / Part Time&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Band 5 Staff Nurse to join our Fracture Clinic and Trauma and Orthopaedic Outpatients team at the Royal Berkshire Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a busy department providing high-quality care to both elective orthopaedic and trauma patients. Our department is open Monday to Friday during day-time hours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is an opportunity for variety in your day including fracture clinics, elective clinics, spoke clinics (Bracknell), Plaster Room and the Virtual Fracture Clinic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and motivated Staff Nurse with effective communication skills to join our friendly team. In return, we will offer ongoing learning opportunities to support your professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal visits are most welcome.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sister Tracey Chapple / Senior Staff Nurse Georgina Bigmore on 0118 322 7550 or tracey.chapple@royalberkshire.nhs.uk / georgina.bigmore@royalberkshire.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
